title: 111_s2379
content: CERTAIN THREE-RING BINDERS WHOLLY OR PREDOMINANTLY COVERED WITH POLYESTER FABRICS. Amendment to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to include new headings in Subchapter II of chapter 99. Amendment to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to include new headings in Subchapter II of chapter 99 for three-ring binders with outer surface covered with polyester fabric and metal rings designed for letter-sized paper. Amendment to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to include new headings in Subchapter II of chapter 99 for three-ring binders with outer surface covered with polyester fabric and metal rings designed for letter-sized paper, measuring approximately 51 mm by 280 mm. Amendment to the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to include new headings in Subchapter II of chapter 99 for three-ring binders with outer surface covered with polyester fabric and metal rings designed for letter-sized paper, measuring approximately 51 mm by 280 mm. Three-ring binders with outer surface covered in polyester fabric and metal rings exceeding 51mm diameter, designed for letter-sized paper. The curr_chunk describes sheets of letter-sized paper with a zipper closure, measuring approximately 51 mm by 280 mm. Three-ring binders with outer surface covered with polyester fabric and metal rings not exceeding 51 mm in diameter, designed for letter-sized paper, with a zipper closure. Three-ring binders with polyester fabric covering and metal rings under 51 mm in diameter, designed for letter-sized paper. Three-ring binders with polyester fabric covering and metal rings under 51 mm in diameter, designed for letter-sized paper, with a hook and loop closure. Three-ring binders with polyester fabric covering and metal rings exceeding 51mm in diameter, designed for letter-sized paper with an elastic band closure. Three-ring binders with metal rings exceeding 51mm in diameter, designed to hold standard letter-sized paper with an elastic band closure. The effective date for the amendment applies to goods entered or withdrawn from warehouse for consumption after the 15th day following the enactment of the Act.
